2. cs.RO (Robotics): The proposed method can be applied to robotics applications such as robot navigation and manipulation. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although the proposed method is model-based and does not rely on training data, it can be seen as a complementary approach to learning-based methods in the field of machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new method for 3D reconstruction, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics): The proposed method can be used for 3D modeling and animation, which is a subfield of computer graphics.
